name: Spar Roll
[config] description: Remove mean from the measured roll rate; integrate using trapezoidal rule
inputs:
Sway Acceleration Corrected
Roll Rate

name: Spar Pitch
[config] description: Remove mean from the measured pitch rate; integrate using trapezoidal rule
inputs:
Surge Acceleration Corrected
Pitch Rate

name: Spar Tilt
[config] description: Spar Tilt = sqrt[(Spar Tilt Platform North)^2 + (Spar Tilt Platform East)^2]
inputs:
Spar Roll
Spar Pitch

name: Spar Tilt Direction
[config] description: Spar Tilt Direction = atan[(Spar Tilt Platform East)/(Spar Tilt Platform North)] + Platform Heading
inputs:
Spar Roll
Spar Pitch

name: 15 Min Avg Spar Roll
[config] description: 15 min running average of roll estimated from accelerations
inputs:
Archive Flag
Spar Roll
Roll Rate
Initial Roll Rate (0.0)

name: 15 Min Avg Spar Pitch
[config] description: 15 min running average of pitch estimated from accelerations
inputs:
Archive Flag
Spar Pitch
Pitch Rate
Initial Pitch Rate (0.0)

name: 15 Min Avg Spar Tilt
[config] description: Spar Tilt formed from 15 Min Avg Spar Roll and 15 Min Avg Spar Pitch
inputs:
Average Spar Roll
Average Spar Pitch

name: 15 Min Avg Spar Tilt Dir
[config] description: Spar tilt Direction formed from 15 min Avg Spar Roll and 15 Min Avg Spar Pitch
inputs:
Average Spar Roll
Average Spar Pitch

name: 30 Min Avg Air Temperature
[config] description: 30 minute running average of Air Temperature
inputs:
Archive Flag
Air Temperature

name: 30 Min Avg Bar. Pressure
[config] description: 30 minute running average of Barometric Pressure
inputs:
Archive Flag
Barometric Pressure

name: 30 Min Sig Wave Ht North
[config] description: Four times the standard deviation of the surface elevation obtained from a rolling 30min record of the quality controlled North Airgap sensor reading
inputs:
Archive Flag
Wave1 North OL
calculation: WinMon Doc: Significant Wave Height - Hs

name: 30 Min Peak Period North
[config] description: 30 minute running average of wave energy peak period
column15: Zero crossing period  obtained from rolling 30min record of the quality controlled North Airgap sensor reading
inputs: Wave1 North OL

name: 30 Min Sig Wave Ht South
[config] description: Four times the standard deviation of the surface elevation obtained from a rolling 30min record of the quality controlled South Airgap sensor reading
inputs:
Archive Flag
Wave2 South OL
calculation: WinMon Doc: Significant Wave Height - Hs

name: 30 Min Peak Period South
[config] description: 30 minute running average of wave energy peak period
column15: Zero crossing period  obtained from rolling 30min record of the quality controlled South Airgap sensor reading
inputs: Wave2 South OL

name: Best 30 Min Sig Wave Ht
[config] description: Maximum of the significant wave height calculated from all available quality controlled air gap readings, which are individually calculated as 4 x standard deviation over a 30min running interval
inputs:
Sig Wave Ht North
Sig Wave Ht South
constants:
Min Height = 0.2
Small Wave = 4.5
Small Ration = 2.4

name: Best 30 Min Peak Period
[config] description: Zero crossing period corresponding to best significant wave height
inputs:
Wave1 North Peak Period
Wave2 South Peak Period
constants:
Min Height = 0.2
Small Wave = 4.5
Small Ration = 2.4

name: Riser A Tension
[config] description: Measures the total axial force acting on Riser A to maintain its vertical position
inputs:
Load Cell 1
Load Cell 2
Load Cell 3

name: Riser A VIV
[config] description: Indicates vortex-induced vibration activity affecting Riser A from ocean currents
inputs:
Riser Tension
Index of Riser
calculation:
Mean1 = RunningAvg(RiserTension, Index of Riser)
Mean2 = RunningAvg(RiserTension^2, Index of Riser)
Mean3 = RunningAvg(RiserTension^3, Index of Riser)
Mean4 = RunningAvg(RiserTension^4, Index of Riser)
Variance = Mean2 - (Mean1^2)
    if (Variance <= VIV Variance Min): VIV = 100
    else : (Mean4 + Mean1 * (-4 * Mean3 + 3 * Mean1 * (2 * Mean2 - (Mean1^2))) / (Variance^2)

name: Riser A N/S Bending
[config] description: Represents the bending moment on Riser A in the North–South direction
inputs:
Load Cell 1
Load Cell 2
Load Cell 3
calculation: LC1 * LC Radius - (LC2 + LC3) * LC Radius * sin(30)

name: Riser A E/W Bending

inputs:
Load Cell 2
Load Cell 3

name: Riser A Freeboard
[config] description: Measures the vertical distance from the waterline to the top of Riser A above the sea surface
constants:
Freeboard Automatic or Manual
Distance to Keel Zero Offset
Riser A Manual Freeboard Override

name: Riser A BC5 Air Gap
[config] description: Distance between the sea surface and buoyancy can 5 on Riser A
inputs:
Freeboard
BC5 Pressure
constants:
BC5 Distance to Top
BC5 Internal Length
FTPERPSI
calculation:
Pressure Offset = BC5 Pressure * 0.016494 - 0.36 (regressed approximation)
Air Gap = Freeboard + (BC5 Pressure + Pressure Offset) * FTPERPSI - BC5 Dist to Top
    if (Air Gap < 0): Air Gap = 0
    else (Air Gap > BC5 Internal Length): Air Gap = BC5 Internal Length

[config] description: Distance between the sea surface and buoyancy can 6 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC7 Air Gap
[config] description: Distance between the sea surface and buoyancy can 7 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC11 Air Gap

name: Riser A BC12 Air Gap
[config] description: Distance between the sea surface and buoyancy can 12 on Riser A
calculation:
Pressure Offset = BC12 Pressure * 0.016494 - 0.36 (regressed approximation)
Air Gap = Freeboard + (BC12 Pressure + Pressure Offset) * FTPERPSI - BC12 Dist to Top
    if (Air Gap < 0): Air Gap = 0
    else (Air Gap > (BC12 Internal Length + Cone Length)): Air Gap = BC12 Internal Length + Cone Length

name: Riser A Stem Air Gap
[config] description: Vertical gap between the sea surface and the lower stem section of Riser A
inputs:
Stem Pressure
Freeboard
calculation: Stem Pressure * FTPERPSI + Freeboard - Stem Dist to Top

name: Riser A BC5 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 5 on Riser A
inputs: BC5 Airgap
constants:
H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3 (density of freshwater)
BC5 Internal Length
BC5 Internal Cross-Sectional Area
BC5 Outer Volume
calculation: (H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3 * (BC5 Outer Volume - BC5 Internal Length - BC5 Airgap) * BC5 ICSA) / 1000

name: Riser A BC6 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 6 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC7 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 7 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC8 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 8 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC9 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 9 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC10 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 10 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC11 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 11 on Riser A

name: Riser A BC12 Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force provided by buoyancy can 12 on Riser A
inputs: BC12 Airgap
constants:
BC12 Internal Length
H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3
BC12 Outer Volume
BC12 Internal Cross-Sectional Area
Cone Outer Volume
Cone Internal Volume
BC12 Inside Diameter
Cone Diameter Slope
Cone Length
PI
BC12 Outside Diameter
Cone Inside Diameter
calculation:
if (BC12 Air Gap  <= BC12 Internal Length)
    BC12 Buoyancy = H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3 * (BC12 Outer Volume - (BC12 ICSA * (BC12 Internal Length - BC12 Airgap)) + (Cone Outer Volume - Cone Internal Volume)) / 1000.0
else
    NewDiameter = BC12 Inside Diameter - Cone Diameter Slope * (BC12 Air Gap - BC12 Internal Length)
    NewLength = BC12 Internal Length + Cone Length - BC12 Air Gap
    StemVolumeSurroundedByH2OInCone = New Length * (PI/4) * (BC12OutsideDiameter^2)
    StemVolumeInCone = Cone Length * (PI/4) * (BC12OutsideDiameter^2)
    NewVolume = (NewLength * (PI/12) * (NewDiameter^2) + (ConeInsideDiameter^2) + (NewDiameter * ConeInsideDiameter))) - StemVolumeSurroundedByH2OInCone
    BC12 Buoyancy = H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3 * (BC12 Outer Volume + Cone Outer Volume - StemVolumeInCone - New Volume) / 1000.0

name: Riser A Stem Buoyancy
[config] description: Upward force from the stem portion of Riser A
inputs:
Stem Airgap
Freeboard
constants:
H2ODEN_LBSPERFT3
Stem Outer Length
Stem Outer Volume
Stem Distance to Top
STEM Internal Cross-Sectional Area
PI
Stem Outside Diameter
Riser Outside Diameter
BC1 Distance to Top
BC1 Outer Length
BC1 Outer Diameter

name: Riser A Total Buoyancy
[config] description: Combined buoyant force from all components of Riser A
inputs:
All  BCx Buoyancies
Stem Buoyancy
BC1 Buoy
calculation: SUM(BCx Buoyancy) + STEM Buoyancy + BC1 Buoy + Other Buoyancy * 3 - System Weight

name: Wave1 North OL
[config] description: Quality controlled distance of the Wave1 North Airgap sensor to the instantaneous water surface
inputs:
Wave1 North
Archive Flag
calculation:
if (Archive Flag): Wave1 North OL = Wave1 North
else: remove_outliers2(Wave1 North) -> WinMon Doc: Air-Gap

name: Wave2 South OL
[config] description: Quality controlled distance of the Wave2 South Airgap sensor to the instantaneous water surface
inputs:
Wave2 South
Archive Flag
calculation:
if (Archive Flag): Wave2 South OL = Wave2 South
else: remove_outliers2(Wave2 South) -> WinMon Doc: Air-Gap

name: 1min 10m EC Wind Speed
[config] description: 1 minute and 10 minute running average of the wind speed measured at East Crane anemometer
column15: 1minute running average of the quality controlled wind speed measured at east crane location, scaled to 10m above MWL elevation
inputs:
Archive Flag
EC Wind Speed

name: 1min 10m WC Wind Speed
[config] description: 1 minute and 10 minute running average of the wind speed measured at West Crane anemometer
column15: 1minute running average of the quality controlled wind speed measured at west crane location, scaled to 10m above MWL elevation
inputs:
Archive Flag
WC Wind Speed

name: 1min 10m Best Wind Speed
[config] description: 1 minute and 10 minute running average of wind speed measured of the selected anemometer
column15: 1minute running average of the highest wind speed from all available wind sensors, scaled to 10m above MWL elevation
inputs:
EC Wind Speed
WC Wind Speed
EC 1min 10m Wind Speed
WC 1min 10m Wind Speed

name: Platform Offset
[config] description: Calculated horizontal plane offset of the platform from the platform reference position
inputs:
COMBO Spar Northings
COMBO Spar Eastings

name: Platform Offset Dir
[config] description: Angle clockwise of True North, of an imaginary line from the platform reference position to the instantaneous platform origin
inputs:
COMBO Spar Northings
COMBO Spar Eastings
calculation: WinMon Doc: Combo PQ Offset Direction
